The paper deals with artwork recommendation using metadata and visual features, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The study also considers user acceptance and explainability, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep neural networks (DNN) for visual feature extraction suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.CL) sub-categories.
